{{Infobox television | show_name = ITV News Summary | image = | format = [[National (distribution)|National]] and [[international]] [[news]] | presenter = | runtime = 2 minutes | producer = [[ITN]] | country = [[United Kingdom]] | network = [[ITV]] <small>([[ITV1]]/[[STV (TV network)|STV]]/[[UTV]])</small> | first_aired = [[September 22]], [[1955]] | last_aired = Present |}} '''''ITV News Summary''''' is a news update on the British television network [[ITV]]. The bulletin, lasting around 2 minutes, is broadcast every day of the week: *Monday to Friday 11:25am (during ''[[This Morning (TV series)|This Morning]]'') :This bulletin is presented by the newscaster of the ''[[ITV News at 1:30]]'' that day (usually [[Alastair Stewart]]); it is followed by an [[ITV Weather|ITV Regional Weather]] forecast.
*Monday to Sunday at various times between 1:00am to 3:00am. :This bulletin is presented by the newscaster of the ''[[ITV News at 5:30]]'' that day (usually [[Faye Barker]] or [[Charlene White]]).
